  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Geometry | Merge Points</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">About Merge-Points</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">When two Points are merged, they become one Point.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">There are commands that need a sketch in which the <text styleclass="Interface">start-Points</text> and/or the <text styleclass="Interface">end-Points</text> of sketch-elements are <text styleclass="VariableName">merged</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">This command is usually used to repair a sketch-path in which two(2) <text styleclass="Element">Points</text> should be merged to one(1) <text styleclass="Element">Point</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="" anchor="HoverTechnique">Hover+Drag technique</link> is much more efficient to use as you add sketch-elements. </para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">Commands that need start-Point and end-Points to be Merged</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-style:italic;">:</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text">To sketch </text><text styleclass="Interface">Closed Sketch-Loops</text> for a <text styleclass="Element">Profile / Extrusion</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text">To sketch </text><text styleclass="Interface">Open</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> or </text><text styleclass="Interface">Closed Sketch-Loop</text> for <text styleclass="Element">Motion-Paths, Belts, motion Guidance</text>.</li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text">To merge the end-Points of the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Gears-Line-of-Centres" styleclass="Body Text">Line-of-Centers</link><text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">for </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Gear-Pair" styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Gear-Trains</link></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso" style="margin-left:0px;">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Sketch-Loop">sketch-path</link>, <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Geometry-Coincident">Add Coincident-Constraint</link>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Merge-Points</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="3" colcount="3">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td rowspan="3" style="width:20px; border-right:none;">
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:center;"><image src="MD-Toolbar-SE-MergePoints.ipp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:middle; width:82px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Toolbar : </para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:middle; width:560px;">
          <para styleclass="T_Menu"><text styleclass="VariableName">Part-Editor :</text> Geometry Toolbar</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:middle">
        <td style="width:82px;">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Menu : </para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:560px;">
          <para styleclass="T_Menu"><text styleclass="VariableName">Part-Editor :</text> Add menu &gt; Geometry sub-menu&gt; &gt; Merge-Points</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">To Merge-Points*</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="PopupTable2" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td style="border-top:none; border-right:none; border-bottom:none;">
                <para styleclass="Body Table">If there are two separate <text styleclass="Interface">Points</text>:</para>
                <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Interface">Part-Editor:</text><text styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">&#32;</text>Click <text styleclass="T_Menu">Geometry-toolbar &gt; Merge-Points</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="text-align:left; text-indent:-24px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.00; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Interface">Part-Editor:</text><text styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">&#32;</text>Click a <text styleclass="Interface">Point*</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> that belongs to a sketch-element </text></li>
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="text-align:left; text-indent:-24px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.00; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Interface">Part-Editor:</text><text styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text">Click a </text><text styleclass="Interface">Point*</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> that belongs to a different sketch-element</text></li>
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="text-align:left; text-indent:-24px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:48px; line-height:1.00; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Interface">Part-Editor:</text><text styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text">Click the </text><text styleclass="Interface">graphic-area</text></li>
                </list>
                <para styleclass="Body Text">OR</para>
                <para styleclass="Body Table">If there are two coincident <text styleclass="Interface">Points</text>, then</para>
                <list id="2" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="Bullets">Click, with one click, the two coincident <text styleclass="Element">Points</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
                  <li styleclass="Bullets">Click <text styleclass="T_Menu">Geometry-toolbar &gt; Merge-Points</text></li>
                </list>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The two <text styleclass="Interface">Points*</text> are now Merged to one <text styleclass="Element">Point</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">* <text styleclass="VariableName">Point</text> - usually <text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text>, <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text>, or <text styleclass="Interface">center-Point</text> of a sketch-element.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Notes">Notes:</para>
          <list id="3" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">You CANNOT merge a <text styleclass="Interface">Point*</text> with the <text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text> or <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text> of a <text styleclass="Element">CAD-Line</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> of an </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Part" styleclass="Interface">Added-Part</link><text styleclass="Interface">. </text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">You CAN, however, merge a <text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text> or <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text> of a sketch-element if you &apos;drag to&apos; or &apos;drag from&apos; the Part&apos;s Origin, (<text styleclass="Element">CAD-Line&apos;s</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Element">start-Point</text>)</li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Merge-Point in the Graphic-Area, Selection-Window and Geometry-Tree.</para>
