          <list id="4" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Two different Points at the end of sketch-elements.</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Click a Point and then a different Point. One Point is deleted (Compare with <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Geometry-Coincident">CoincidentPtoP</link><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Geometry-Coincident" style="text-decoration:underline;">)</link>, and the sketch-elements move together.</para>
